The object to compute is the contact term part of the expression $\partial_x^\mu \partial_y^ho \langle \mathcal{T} B_{\mu
u}(x) B_{ho\sigma}(y) angle$.
We start with the given momentum space representation of the two-point function:
$$
\partial_x^\mu \partial_y^ho \langle \mathcal{T} B_{\mu
u}(x) B_{ho\sigma}(y) angle = \int  rac{d^D p}{(2\pi)^D} e^{-ip(x-y)} \left( p^\mu p^ho i\Delta_{\mu
u,ho\sigma}(p) ight)
$$
Let's compute the momentum-space expression $\mathcal{C}_{
u\sigma}(p) = p^\mu p^ho i\Delta_{\mu
u,ho\sigma}(p)$.
We contract $p^\mu p^ho$ with the two parts of the propagator:
1.  Contraction with the first part:
    $p^\mu p^ho  rac{i}{p^2} \left[  rac{1}{2}(\eta_{\muho}\eta_{
u\sigma} - \eta_{\mu\sigma}\eta_{
uho}) ight] =  rac{i}{2p^2}(p^2\eta_{
u\sigma} - p_
u p_\sigma) =  rac{i}{2}(\eta_{
u\sigma} -  rac{p_
u p_\sigma}{p^2})$.
2.  Contraction with the second part:
    $p^\mu p^ho  rac{-i(1-\xi)}{p^4} (p_\mu p_ho \eta_{
u\sigma} - p_\mu p_\sigma \eta_{
uho} - p_
u p_ho \eta_{\mu\sigma} + p_
u p_\sigma \eta_{\muho}) =  rac{-i(1-\xi)}{p^4} (p^4 \eta_{
u\sigma} - p^2 p_
u p_\sigma) = -i(1-\xi)(\eta_{
u\sigma} -  rac{p_
u p_\sigma}{p^2})$.

Summing these two results gives the full expression:
 egin{align*}
\mathcal{C}_{
u\sigma}(p) &=  rac{i}{2}(\eta_{
u\sigma} -  rac{p_
u p_\sigma}{p^2}) - i(1-\xi)(\eta_{
u\sigma} -  rac{p_
u p_\sigma}{p^2}) \
&= i\left( rac{1}{2} - 1 + \xiight)(\eta_{
u\sigma} -  rac{p_
u p_\sigma}{p^2}) \
&= i\left(\xi -  rac{1}{2}ight)(\eta_{
u\sigma} -  rac{p_
u p_\sigma}{p^2})
\end{align*}
Contact terms in position space correspond to terms that are polynomials in momentum in momentum space. We can split $\mathcal{C}_{
u\sigma}(p)$ into a polynomial part and a non-polynomial part:
$$
\mathcal{C}_{
u\sigma}(p) = i \left( \xi -  rac{1}{2} ight) \eta_{
u\sigma} - i \left( \xi -  rac{1}{2} ight)  rac{p_
u p_\sigma}{p^2}
$$
The first term is a constant in momentum (a degree-0 polynomial). Its Fourier transform will produce a delta function, which is a contact term. The second term is not a polynomial and corresponds to a non-local contribution in position space.

The contact term contribution is the Fourier transform of the polynomial part of $\mathcal{C}_{
u\sigma}(p)$:
$$
	ext{Contact Terms} = \int  rac{d^D p}{(2\pi)^D} e^{-ip(x-y)} \left[ i \left( \xi -  rac{1}{2} ight) \eta_{
u\sigma} ight]
$$
Using the integral representation of the Dirac delta function, $\int  rac{d^D p}{(2\pi)^D} e^{-ip(x-y)} = \delta^D(x-y)$, we get:
$$
	ext{Contact Terms} = i \left( \xi -  rac{1}{2} ight) \eta_{
u\sigma} \delta^D(x-y)
$$
